    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-11-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-11-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="465"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d465">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 711.428/453</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The British Ambassador</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Spring Rice</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 519</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-11-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 17, 1917</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honour to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your note No. 1889 of November 13, the substance of which I have communicated to
                    the Canadian Government.</p>
                <p>With reference to the last paragraph thereof, I have the honour to inform you
                    that it is my understanding also that the representatives of the two countries
                    are only to be empowered to come to a mutually satisfactory understanding as to
                    all pending questions, and to report the result of their deliberations to their
                    respective Governments as a basis for the subsequent negotiation of a formal
                    agreement.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cecil Spring Rice</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
